  "enhanced_information": "Renin is produced by juxtaglomerular cells in the kidneys and is involved in blood pressure regulation, confirming it is produced by the renal system. Angiotensin I is not directly produced by the kidneys; it is formed from angiotensinogen, which is produced in the liver, and is converted to angiotensin II primarily in the lungs, thus supporting that it is not a renal product. Erythropoietin is produced by interstitial fibroblasts in the kidneys and stimulates red blood cell production, confirming it is a renal product. 1,25-Dihydroxyvitamin D (1,25DHCC) is the active form of vitamin D produced in the kidneys from calcidiol, confirming it is also a renal product. Therefore, the peptide not produced by the renal system is Angiotensin I."
